text: Sayidiman Suryohadiprojo (21 September 1927 â€” 16 January 2021) was an Indonesian Javanese Army lieutenant general and politician. He was an Ambassador to Japan from 1979 until 1983 and Ambassador-at-large to Africa from 1992 until 1995. Suryohadiprojo was born in Bojonegoro Regency, East Java. Suryohadiprojo died on 16 January 2021 at a Jakarta hospital, aged 93. ==References== Category:1927 births Category:2021 deaths Category:Indonesian military people Category:Indonesian politicians Category:Ambassadors of Indonesia
